{"title_page": "Leo Aberer", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|Name= Leo Aberer\n|image=Leo_Aberer.JPG\n|landscape = yes\n|Caption= Leo Aberer\n|Alias= LeeOne.com, Leo\n|Background= solo_singer\n|birth_date= {{Birth date and age|df=y|1978|03|27}}\n|Origin=[[Vienna]], [[Austria]]\n|Occupation= [[Singer-songwriter]], musician\n|Instrument= [[Singing|Vocals]], [[guitar]], [[violin]], [[synthesizer]]\n|Genre= [[Pop music|Pop]], [[blues]], [[reggae]], [[Swing music|swing]], [[hip hop music|hip hop]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[alternative rock]]\n|Years_active= 1999-present\n|Associated_acts= [[Patricia Kaiser]], [[LL Cool J]], [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]], [[Laith Al-Deen]], [[Jetzt Anders]], [[Lia Weller]], [[Marco Angelini]], [[Simone Kopmajer]]\n|Website= [http://www.leoaberer.eu/ Official Website]\n}}\n\n'''Leo Aberer''' (born in [[Vienna]] on March 27, 1978),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/858270da-8a2d-4032-8e6c-d552c7995b2c|title=Leo Aberer - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> also \"Leo\" or \"Leeone\", is an [[Austria]]n pop singer. He became famous through his participation in the  [[\u00d63 soundcheck]] during the year 2005, the [[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]]-Show The Match and the preliminary decision of [[Eurovision Song Contest]] 2011 with [[Patricia Kaiser]].\n\n== Education ==\nLeo Aberer has received [[violin]] lessons since he was seven years old at the [[Vienna Konservatorium]].  Moreover, he plays [[guitar]] and [[Musical keyboard|keyboard]] after he had taught it himself. During the following years he studied [[jazz]] at [[Universit\u00e4t Graz|Karl-Franzens-Universit\u00e4t]] in [[Graz]]. At the same time he studied Business Administration and [[Psychology]].\n\n== Biography ==\nIn 2003 he recorded his first album and also his debut single called \u201cSterne\u201d (German for \"stars\").  Both allowed him the entrance into the Austrian charts with position 69 (album) and 21 for his first single. \nWhen participating in the [[\u00d63 soundcheck]] 2005, he reached the second place and received a new record deal at [[Universal Music]]. Together with his band he tours through Austria since 2066. During the same year his single \u201cWon\u00b4t you know\u201d was part of the Austrian charts for more than 20 weeks. Later he published songs such as \u201cWalking and Talking\u201d. \nIn 2007 Leo Aberer was nominated for [[Amadeus Austrian Music Award]].<ref>[http://www.sra.at/band/32654 Nominierung] (als ''Leo'') zum [[Amadeus Austrian Music Award]]</ref>\n\nAs part of the initiative ''[[Die Neuen \u00d6sterreicher]]'' Leo Aberer recorded the single \u201cKinder\u201d (German for \"children\") in November 2007 together with other musicians. Their whole benefit was donated to an Austrian charity project called ''[[Licht ins Dunkel]]''.\n\nIn 2013 he entered a new part of music business with opening his own music label \"Black Baracuda\" and publishing house \"Leoversum\" in Austria.\n\nLeo Aberer\u00b4s video for the song \u201cSweet honey\u201d reached no 14 on the international YouTube -charts on 26 March 2008.<ref>[http://oe3.orf.at/dieneuenoesterreicher/stories/264950/ oe3.orf.at]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2010, he reinterpreted it together with [[Laith al Deen]]. After he had recorded his longplayer \u201cSackgasse\u201d he left Austria and went to Los Angeles. There, he started working with rapper [[LL Cool J]] and recorded his new album.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120711230730/http://oe3.orf.at/aktuell/stories/420372/ oe3.orf.at / Aktuell]</ref>\n\nIn 2010 his album \u201cWann geda?\u201d was published and made up the first charts entry for Leo Aberer for years. During the same year Leo Aberer published the song \u201cI wanna be free\u201d.\n\nIn fall of the year 2010 he won the public vote for the Austrian preliminary decision to the [[Eurovision Song Contest]] 2011, together with Patricia Kaiser and the song \u201cThere Will Never Be Another You\u201d.<ref>[http://www.krone.at/Stars-Society/Leo_Aberer_und_Patricia_Kaiser_gewinnen_Voting-Song_Contest_2011-Story-243399 1.Platz]</ref> \u201cThere will Never be Another You\u201d became No 1 in the charts some days later.\n\n \nIn May 2012 Aberer travelled to [[New York City]] and [[Budapest]] where he produced the song \u201cFootball is my life\u201d in collaboration with [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]]. It became the official song for [[European championships]] in 2012\nMoreover, he recorded the song \u201cGiovanna\u201d which entered the charts immediately (No 5 during the year 2013)\n\nIn May 2014 he got the \u201cErzherzog-Johann-Award\u201d which is related to the charity project \u201cBand f\u00fcr Steiermark\u201d\n\nAnother cooperation with Shaggy took place during the [[World Championships]] in the year 2014 with the song \"Football Minha Vida\"..\n\nLast but not least he started a new project in November 2014. In collaboration with [[Marco Angelini]] he recorded the song \u201cGoodbye\u201d which conducts the iTunes Charts since its publication. \u201cGoodbye\u201d reached chart position No. 9 and was part of the official Austrian Charts for weeks.\n\n2018/2019 Leo Aberer discovered [[Africa]]. He was live on stage in great shows at [[CNN]], Ten over 10, Citizen, [[Kenya Broadcasting Corporation]], K24, Arena 254, Trend, Ktn, Mseto and became famous as \"PAPA LEO\". By the way, he helps and supports children in a school in [[Ukunda]].\n\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"200\">\nFile: Shaggy leo.JPG|Aberer with Shaggy\nFile: Leo Aberer 3.jpg|Leo Aberer\nFile: Leo Aberer - Sackgasse.jpg|\"Sackgasse\"\nFile: Football is my life.JPG|Minha Vida \u2013 World Championship 2014\n\n</gallery>\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" width=\"10\"|Year\n!align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" width=\"220\"|Album\n!align=\"center\" colspan=\"1\" width=\"20\"|Peak positions\n!align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\" width=\"70\"|Certification\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br><ref name=\"aut\">{{cite web | url=http://austriancharts.at/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Leo+Aberer | title=Leo Aberer discography | publisher=Hung Medien | work=austriancharts.at |accessdate=4 November 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2006\n|''Sterne'' <small>(as Leo)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|69\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|''Spielball'' <small>(as Leo)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{spaced ndash}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2009\n|''Sackgasse'' <small>(as Leo Aberer)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{spaced ndash}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n|''Wann geda?'' <small>(as Leo Aberer)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|46\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2013\n|''Ego State L1114'' <small>(as Leo Aberer)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{spaced ndash}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n|}\n\n;Others\n*2002: ''Walking and Talking'' (independent release)\n*2003: ''Sterne'' (independent release)\n\n== Discografie ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Titel !! Interpret !! Jahr !! Anmerkung\n|-\n| Back in Time || Leoone || 1999 || \n|-\n| Sterne || Leo || 2003 || \n|-\n| Won\u2019t You Know || Leo Aberer || 2006 || \n|-\n| Baby ist das Liebe || Leo Aberer || 2006 || [[Bravo Hits]] 55\n|-\n| Walking and Talking || Leo Aberer ||2006 || \n|-\n| Dancing || Leo Aberer ||2007 || \n|-\n| Rollin || Inez & Leo Aberer || 2007 || \n|-\n| Sweet Honey || Leo Aberer || 2008; 2010 || featuring [[Laith Al-Deen]] & [[Johnny Palmer]]\n|-\n| What About the Rain || Leo Aberer || 2009 || \n|-\n| Wanna Be Happy || Leo Aberer || 2009 || \n|-\n